00:02:30,127 --> 00:02:32,186
and let's begin using that.

64
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:33,251
See it?

65
00:02:33,251 --> 00:02:34,338
It sort of matches all this, it sort of

66
00:02:34,338 --> 00:02:36,123
works together.

67
00:02:36,508 --> 00:02:38,192
It's really a gorgeous brown.

68
00:02:39,777 --> 00:02:41,058
All right.

69
00:02:41,058 --> 00:02:43,954
And some on the other side,

70
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:46,067
just right in there.

71
00:02:47,686 --> 00:02:49,403
And then we'll finish the canvas up.

72
00:02:50,288 --> 00:02:52,340
We'll just use a little vandyke brown.

73
00:02:53,191 --> 00:02:54,807
Little bit on the other side.

74
00:02:57,596 --> 00:02:59,681
And we're ready to wash the old brush.

75
00:03:00,699 --> 00:03:02,100
As you know if you've
painted with me before,

