00:03:34,799 --> 00:03:37,218
if you cover the living room with paint.

90
00:03:37,635 --> 00:03:39,752
I'm just blending all
these colors together,

91
00:03:41,271 --> 00:03:42,322
like so.

92
00:03:43,275 --> 00:03:45,593
All right, and then I'm going
to wash the brush again.

93
00:03:46,477 --> 00:03:49,430
I'm really just looking for
excuses to wash the brush.

94
00:03:52,015 --> 00:03:53,700
(laughs) There we are.

95
00:03:54,019 --> 00:03:56,387
Now then, I want to
brighten that a little more,

96
00:03:56,387 --> 00:03:59,639
so I'll go right into titanium white.

97
00:04:00,525 --> 00:04:02,576
We just put a little
on the two inch brush.

98
00:04:03,527 --> 00:04:04,828
Go right up in here.

99
00:04:04,829 --> 00:04:08,314
Start in the lightest area,
and begin working outward.

100
00:04:09,766 --> 00:04:12,257
We want this to be the
lightest, brightest part

101
00:04:12,257 --> 00:04:14,323
of this whole painting, right here.

102
00:04:15,073 --> 00:04:16,120
There.

